no it doesnt, as i have learnt, the minimap fields are, the angle of the map relative to fixed north, the angle offset from the Y axis and the compass scale

Also:

*getCompassCurveArrayY() into class client returns STATIC int[] hb.eb *getCompassCurveArrayX() into class client returns STATIC int[] hb.W

this is more suited to “Mobile” (thanks frank_) as its a Mobile Entity, and if you dont know what that is, lol @ you.

dear oh dear, this is poorly named here, not doing so well are we?
“getMyPlayerEntity” isn’t as poorly named as the others, but i will come onto that. i call this “LocalPlayer”

now for getLocationX and getLocationY, OUCH can you say?
that naming makes ZERO sence.
heres a code snippet from the client, maybe you can put it to some use rather then “pretending” to know howto name fields. YUK

public void setPosition(int x, int y, boolean isWalking) { if(animation != -1 && Class13.method134(!isWalking, animation).anInt3143 == 1) animation = -1; int ydistance = y - walkingQueueY[0]; int xdistance = x - walkingQueueX[0]; if(isWalking) if(xdistance >= -8 && xdistance <= 8 && ydistance >= -8 && ydistance <= 8) { if(distance < 9) distance++; for(int i1 = distance; i1 > 0; i1--) { walkingQueueX[i1] = walkingQueueX[i1 - 1]; walkingQueueY[i1] = walkingQueueY[i1 - 1]; aBooleanArray3841[i1] = aBooleanArray3841[i1 - 1]; } aBooleanArray3841[0] = false; walkingQueueX[0] = x; walkingQueueY[0] = y; return; } distance = 0; walkingQueueX[0] = x; walkingQueueY[0] = y; this.x = 128 * walkingQueueX[0] + anInt3833 * 64; this.y = 64 * anInt3833 + walkingQueueY[0] * 128; }

also, question
why

*getCharacterX() into class oh returns FIELD int oh.sc *getCharacterY() into class oh returns FIELD int oh.Zb,
why not just name them X and Y, you inject them into the misnomered character class, its just useless characters for no reason, trying to look smart by not following convention. well let me tell you, until you understand it (im not saying i do), you CANNOT name anything “correctly”, but with experience you can name them sensibly.

none of us know the official jagex naming schema, and if someone says they do, they are lying.

*getWorldLocationX() into class client returns STATIC int ki.cb *getWorldLocationY() into class client returns STATIC int eb.t
this is really the loaded reigon, 104x104

over and out.

edit: probably numerous spelling mistakes etc etc, but do i give a fuck? no. if you try correct me then your an arse[/quote]

Thank you.
